<collectingCountry id="618D268E4032FFAC0FADFA1BFEDCFA3E" box="[219,330,1445,1466]" name="Ukraine" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">UKRAINE</collectingCountry>
: 
<location id="1C4530C54032FFAC0E25FA1BFE23FA3E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:9133D7084032FFAD0FFEFAC3FD7BF882:1C4530C54032FFAC0E25FA1BFE23FA3E" box="[339,437,1445,1467]" country="Ukraine" county="Bug" municipality="Dnepr" name="Black Sea" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Black Sea</location>
, northwest region in the river mouth of 
<collectingMunicipality id="F941FC644032FFAC0C47FA18FCFBFA3F" box="[817,877,1446,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Dnepr</collectingMunicipality>
and 
<collectingCounty id="F0441E924032FFAC0CEDFA18FC55FA3F" box="[923,963,1446,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Bug</collectingCounty>
(
<typeStatus id="C621D8BC4032FFAC0CA6FA1BFBBDFA3F" box="[976,1067,1445,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Holotype</typeStatus>
<figureCitation id="81A17A9B4032FFAC0B46FA1BFBFCFA3E" box="[1072,1130,1445,1467]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-4" captionStartId="1.[136,243,839,861]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetId="figure-35@1.[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-4. Chaetoceros heterovalvatus. LM fresh preparation, complete cell (1), LM fresh preparation, vaulted valve with curved setae (2), SEM vaulted valve with curved setae (3), SEM valve with divergent setae and rimoportula (arrow) (4), Scale bar 10 µm (1,2), 2 µm (3,4)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501332/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
!, (10 illustrations) in Proschkina-Lavrenko 1953, p. 47)
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1925661E4032FFAC0FFEF9B1FB97F917" blockId="0.[136,1452,1551,2044]" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="2BEEBA0C4032FFAC0FFEF9B1FEC5F9A3" bold="true" box="[136,339,1551,1575]" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">
<collectionCode id="7F8BFEDB4032FFAC0FFEF9B1FF25F9A3" box="[136,179,1551,1575]" country="Mozambique" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13988" name="Secçáo de Botânica e Ecologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="100" type="Herbarium">LM</collectionCode>
observations:
</emphasis>
The cells are solitary, cylindrical with 4 long setae (
<figureCitation id="81A17A9B4032FFAC0CF4F9B1FC57F9A3" box="[898,961,1551,1575]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-4" captionStartId="1.[136,243,839,861]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetId="figure-35@1.[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-4. Chaetoceros heterovalvatus. LM fresh preparation, complete cell (1), LM fresh preparation, vaulted valve with curved setae (2), SEM vaulted valve with curved setae (3), SEM valve with divergent setae and rimoportula (arrow) (4), Scale bar 10 µm (1,2), 2 µm (3,4)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501332/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The frustule is heterovalvate, with a convex valve with the setae rising from the valve margin and directed to the opposite valve with an increasing angle to the pervalvar axis (
<figureCitation id="81A17A9B4032FFAC0FB7F9E9FE94F9EB" box="[193,258,1623,1647]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-4" captionStartId="1.[136,243,839,861]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetId="figure-35@1.[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-4. Chaetoceros heterovalvatus. LM fresh preparation, complete cell (1), LM fresh preparation, vaulted valve with curved setae (2), SEM vaulted valve with curved setae (3), SEM valve with divergent setae and rimoportula (arrow) (4), Scale bar 10 µm (1,2), 2 µm (3,4)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501332/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); the other valve is flat with the setae rising from the margin of the valve and diverging. The apical axis measures 3.2–9.5 µm, and the pervalvar axis 8–12 µm. It contains several small chloroplasts.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1925661E4032FFAC0FCBF921FABDF8C3" blockId="0.[136,1452,1551,2044]" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="2BEEBA0C4032FFAC0FCBF921FE00F933" bold="true" box="[189,406,1695,1719]" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">SEM observations:</emphasis>
Only valves were observed. 
<collectionCode id="7F8BFEDB4032FFAC0DBEF921FD4CF933" box="[712,730,1695,1719]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="0" pageNumber="100" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
valve is vaulted with a smooth mantle with the setae rising between the valve surface and the mantle, curved downwards (
<figureCitation id="81A17A9B4032FFAC0DBFF97DFC9DF95F" box="[713,779,1731,1755]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-4" captionStartId="1.[136,243,839,861]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetId="figure-35@1.[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-4. Chaetoceros heterovalvatus. LM fresh preparation, complete cell (1), LM fresh preparation, vaulted valve with curved setae (2), SEM vaulted valve with curved setae (3), SEM valve with divergent setae and rimoportula (arrow) (4), Scale bar 10 µm (1,2), 2 µm (3,4)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501332/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The other valve is slightly convex whose transition to a wide mantle is abrupt (
<figureCitation id="81A17A9B4032FFAC0E34F959FE12F97B" box="[322,388,1767,1791]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-4" captionStartId="1.[136,243,839,861]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetId="figure-35@1.[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-4. Chaetoceros heterovalvatus. LM fresh preparation, complete cell (1), LM fresh preparation, vaulted valve with curved setae (2), SEM vaulted valve with curved setae (3), SEM valve with divergent setae and rimoportula (arrow) (4), Scale bar 10 µm (1,2), 2 µm (3,4)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501332/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). At the center has a rimoportula composed by a short tube (
<figureCitation id="81A17A9B4032FFAC0B70F959FBDEF97B" box="[1030,1096,1767,1791]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-4" captionStartId="1.[136,243,839,861]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetId="figure-35@1.[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-4. Chaetoceros heterovalvatus. LM fresh preparation, complete cell (1), LM fresh preparation, vaulted valve with curved setae (2), SEM vaulted valve with curved setae (3), SEM valve with divergent setae and rimoportula (arrow) (4), Scale bar 10 µm (1,2), 2 µm (3,4)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501332/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). The setae rise at the edge of the valve surface and mantle diverging perpendicularly to the valve surface. No other ornamentation was observed. The setae are cylindrical at the base and quadrangular (four sided) most of the length with conspicuous spines (
<figureCitation id="81A17A9B4032FFAC0BCBF891FA88F8C3" box="[1213,1310,1839,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-4" captionStartId="1.[136,243,839,861]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetId="figure-35@1.[340,1247,188,813]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-4. Chaetoceros heterovalvatus. LM fresh preparation, complete cell (1), LM fresh preparation, vaulted valve with curved setae (2), SEM vaulted valve with curved setae (3), SEM valve with divergent setae and rimoportula (arrow) (4), Scale bar 10 µm (1,2), 2 µm (3,4)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501332/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="100">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
